cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with optimizing transmission energy in LTE HetNets, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimizing the association between User Equipments (UEs) and cells, which can be seen as an information theory problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The load coupling model used in the paper can be seen as a control problem, where the cells interfere with one another. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The optimization problem in the paper can be seen as a game theory problem, where each cell provides data service for its users so as to maintain a target Quality-of-Service (QoS). 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with optimizing transmission energy for data service, which can be seen as a multimedia problem.
